metadata.name: Before Time
metadata.description:
Before time, before the first second
The universe lay dormant, a vast expanse.
No stars twinkled, no planets spun
No galaxies formed, life hadn't begun.

But within this void, a spark of light
Ignited, a cosmic fire burning bright.
And with this flame, time began to flow
Creating space, and matter, and all we know.

From this primordial fire, so fierce and hot
Came forth the universe, all that we've got.
So let us give thanks for the gift of time,
For the past, the present and all that lies ahead in its climb.
